soc.message

Enum SOCGameElements.GEType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<SOCGameElements.GEType>
      • soc.message.SOCGameElements.GEType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<SOCGameElements.GEType>
    Enclosing class:
    SOCGameElements

    public static enum SOCGameElements.GEType
extends java.lang.Enum<SOCGameElements.GEType>
    Game element type list. To send over the network as an int, use getValue(). When received from network as int, use valueOf(int) to convert to SOCGameElements.GEType.

    Converted from int constants to enum in v2.3.00 for cleaner design and human-readable serialization for SavedGameModel.

    Since:
    2.3.00

      • ROUND_COUNT

        public static final SOCGameElements.GEType ROUND_COUNT

      • DEV_CARD_COUNT

        public static final SOCGameElements.GEType DEV_CARD_COUNT
        Number of development cards remaining in the deck to be bought, from SOCGame.getNumDevCards().

        Sent to clients during game join/start. When a dev card is bought, is sent to clients as part of game data before action announcement/display: See SOCBuyDevCardRequest javadoc.

        Versions before v2.0.00 sent SOCDevCardCount instead.

      • FIRST_PLAYER

        public static final SOCGameElements.GEType FIRST_PLAYER
        Player number of first player in this game, from SOCGame.getFirstPlayer().

        Versions before v2.0.00 sent SOCFirstPlayer instead.

      • CURRENT_PLAYER

        public static final SOCGameElements.GEType CURRENT_PLAYER
        Player number of current player, or -1, from SOCGame.getCurrentPlayerNumber().

        Versions before v2.0.00 sent SOCSetTurn instead.

      • LARGEST_ARMY_PLAYER

        public static final SOCGameElements.GEType LARGEST_ARMY_PLAYER
        Player number of player with Largest Army, or -1, from SOCGame.getPlayerWithLargestArmy(). Sent when client joins a game, and when changes occur during normal gameplay in response to a player's SOCPlayDevCardRequest(KNIGHT).

        In versions before v2.4.00, was not sent by server during game play when Largest Army player changed: Client updated that display by examining game state; see SOCPlayerElement.PEType.NUMKNIGHTS javadoc. Such clients can be sent this element during gameplay, they'll process it just like newer clients do.

        Versions before v2.0.00 sent SOCLargestArmy instead of this element.

      • LONGEST_ROAD_PLAYER

        public static final SOCGameElements.GEType LONGEST_ROAD_PLAYER
        Player number of player with Longest Road/Route, or -1, from SOCGame.getPlayerWithLongestRoad(). Sent when client joins a game, and when changes occur during normal gameplay in response to a player's SOCPutPiece, SOCMovePiece, or SOCDebugFreePlace.

        In versions before v2.4.00, was not sent by server during game play when Longest Route player changed: Client updated that display by examining game state; see SOCPutPiece javadoc section on SOCPlayingPiece.ROAD. Such clients can be sent this element during gameplay, they'll process it just like newer clients do.

        Versions before v2.0.00 sent SOCLongestRoad instead of this element.

      • SPECIAL_BUILDING_AFTER_PLAYER

        public static final SOCGameElements.GEType SPECIAL_BUILDING_AFTER_PLAYER
        During 6-player game's Special Building Phase, the value of SOCGame.getSpecialBuildingPlayerNumberAfter().

        Not sent to clients over network; used only by SavedGameModel when gameState is GameState.SPECIAL_BUILDING.

        Since:
        2.3.00
